f(\theta) = r(\theta)\max\{\sin \theta, \cos \theta\}
f
f_x(\theta) = r(\theta) \sin \theta = \sin \theta + \sin \theta \cos \theta
f_y(\theta) = r(\theta) \cos \theta = \cos \theta + \cos^2 \theta
f_x' = \cos \theta + \cos 2\theta = 2\cos \frac{3\theta}{2} \cos \frac{\theta}{2}
f_y' = -\sin \theta (1+2\cos \theta)
